    "notes": "Kempston joystick read (JOY-KEMPSTON-PORT-001 / -READ-001, dna/domain/peripherals.md). Active-high 000FUDLR: idle 0x00, R=0x01 L=0x02 D=0x04 U=0x08 F=0x10, top three bits always 0 (all-pressed = 0x1F, not 0xFF). Independent controls (Left+Right = 0x03 allowed). Port decode = low byte 0x1F (high byte don't-care: 0x011F and 0xDF1F both decode; 0x1E/0x1D/0x3F/0xFF do not). Pinned hardware per ADR-0021 (F1); finer A5-only aliasing is out of scope. Ships in @zx-vibes/ula beside the floating-bus model — the Kempston is what carves 0x1F out of the floating odd-port set (ULA-FLOATBUS-PORT-001)."
